"title": "8782: mockery",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8782: mockery",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>A form of ridicule directed especially against individuals, with the purpose of humiliating them.  Scripture condemns mockers as arrogant, unrighteous and foolish.</p>\n<h2>Targets of mockery</h2>\n<h3>God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa52:5\">ISA 52:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps74:10\">PSA 74:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps74:18\">PSA 74:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps74:22\">PSA 74:22</a></p>\n<h3>Job</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job30:1\">JOB 30:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job17:2\">JOB 17:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job21:3\">JOB 21:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job30:9\">JOB 30:9</a></p>\n<h3>God's servants</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr36:16\">2CH 36:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh2:19\">NEH 2:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps22:7\">PSA 22:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps35:15-Ps35:16\">PSA 35:15–35:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps69:12\">PSA 69:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps80:6\">PSA 80:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps89:50-Ps89:51\">PSA 89:50–89:51</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps119:51\">PSA 119:51</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer20:7\">JER 20:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam3:14\">LAM 3:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam3:63\">LAM 3:63</a>ACT <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam2:13\">2:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts17:32\">ACT 17:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts26:24\">ACT 26:24</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt20:17-Matt20:19\">MAT 20:17–20:19</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:32-Mark10:34\">MRK 10:32–10:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:31-Luke18:33\">LUK 18:31–18:33</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:67-Matt26:68\">MAT 26:67–26:68</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:65\">MRK 14:65</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:63-Luke22:65\">LUK 22:63–22:65</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:11\">LUK 23:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:27-Matt27:31\">MAT 27:27–27:31</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:16-Mark15:20\">MRK 15:16–15:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:41-Matt27:44\">MAT 27:41–27:44</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:31-Mark15:32\">MRK 15:31–15:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:35\">LUK 23:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:36\">LUK 23:36</a></p>\n<h2>Those who oppose God will become objects of mockery</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov3:34\">PRO 3:34</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs19:20-2Kgs19:28\">2KI 19:20–19:28</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa37:22-Isa37:29\">ISA 37:22–37:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job22:17-Job22:20\">JOB 22:17–22:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer10:14-Jer10:16\">JER 10:14–10:16</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer51:17-Jer51:19\">JER 51:17–51:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek22:1-Ezek22:5\">EZK 22:1–22:5</a></p>\n<h2>False accusations of mockery</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job11:1-Job11:3\">JOB 11:1–11:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job9:21-Job9:24\">JOB 9:21–9:24</a> <em>Job accuses God of mocking the plight of innocent sufferers.</em></p>\n<h2>Mockery in metaphorical use</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov20:1\">PRO 20:1</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Characteristics of mockers</h2>\n<h3>They are proud and arrogant</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov21:24\">PRO 21:24</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov3:34\">PRO 3:34</a></p>\n<h3>They instigate strife</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov22:10\">PRO 22:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov9:7\">PRO 9:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov29:8\">PRO 29:8</a></p>\n<h3>They do not respond to correction</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov15:12\">PRO 15:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov1:22-Prov1:26\">PRO 1:22–1:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov13:1\">PRO 13:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov19:25\">PRO 19:25</a></p>\n<h2>Scripture condemns mockers as unrighteous</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps1:1\">PSA 1:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov14:6\">PRO 14:6</a> <em>Resistance to correction accounts for the failure to find wisdom</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov14:9\">PRO 14:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov24:9\">PRO 24:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa57:4\">ISA 57:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos7:5\">HOS 7:5</a></p>\n<h2>Mockers will be punished</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov1:22-Prov1:26\">PRO 1:22–1:26</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov9:12\">PRO 9:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov17:5\">PRO 17:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov19:28-Prov19:29\">PRO 19:28–19:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov21:11\">PRO 21:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov30:17\">PRO 30:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa28:22\">ISA 28:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa29:20\">ISA 29:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zeph2:10-Zeph2:11\">ZEP 2:10–2:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal6:7\">GAL 6:7</a></p>",
